                        "id": "18107397295578387",
                        "text": "\ud83c\uddef\ud83c\uddf5What will be your list for your next trip in Japan?\ud83c\uddef\ud83c\uddf5\n\nJAPAN\u2019S BEST BURGERS OF 2025\n\n@oneblogram \u25c0 Discover More Hidden Food Spots in Japan! \ud83c\uddef\ud83c\uddf5\n\n\u2460\n\ud83d\udccd NY Bistro by NoCode\nShin-Marunouchi Building 7F, 1-5-1 Marunouchi, Chiyoda-ku, Tokyo, Japan\u00a0\n\nThis Michelin-level bistro just opened in Marunouchi, Tokyo! At NY Bistro by NoCode, you can experience the flavors of NYC, created by Chef Fumio Yonezawa, the first Japanese sous-chef at Jean-Georges, a 3-star Michelin restaurant in NYC for 12 consecutive years.\n\nThis Premium Kobe Beef Burger is on another level! A 180g Kobe beef patty, crispy on the outside and juicy medium-rare inside, bursts with rich umami. It\u2019s perfectly balanced with sweet Awajishima Mitsutama onions, a touch of Fuchu salt from Japan\u2019s lunar tide, and fragrant Edo-grown herbs. Their homemade teriyaki sauce, crafted with Kagawa\u2019s Kamebishi soy sauce, ties everything together beautifully. Each bite was so good and I can\u2019t wait to try other burgers soon!\n\n\u201cCashless Only\u201d\n\n\ud83c\udf54Premium Kobe Beef Burger\n\u2014\n\n\u2461\n\ud83d\udccdBRISKSTAND ASAKUSA\n2 Chome-9-16 Kotobuki, Taito City, Tokyo 111-0042, Japan\n\nTucked away in a quiet alley in Asakusa, this burger shop is changing the game for meat lovers.\n\nThey start with thick, juicy Wagyu patties and melty cheese\u2014\nbut here\u2019s the twist: they grill the cut burger flat-side down in its own juices!\nThe result? A crispy, golden crust and an explosion of flavor in every bite.\n\n\ud83c\udf54Cut Double Patty\n\u2014\n\n\u2462\n\ud83d\udccd WAGYU BROTHERS\nTokyo, Taito City, Asakusa 1-18-3 Endo Bldg. 2F\n\nI just found a burger in Asakusa that literally surprised me.\nIt\u2019s made with A5 Zabuton Wagyu steak.\n\nThe chuck cut is known for its buttery texture and rich flavor, and they grind it fresh into homemade patties. Every bite is insanely tender, packed with pure umami.\nAnd that cheese\u2026 it doesn\u2019t just melt, it falls over the burger in a glorious stream.\n\nDon\u2019t miss the crispy chicken side\u2014it\u2019s so thick and juicy, the crunch alone will hook you.\n\n\ud83c\udf54A5 ZABUTON WAGYU STEAK BURGER\n\u2014\n\n\ud83c\udf40 SAVE this post for your next Tokyo burger run! \ud83c\udf40\n\n/ Japanese Burger / Tokyo Wagyu / Hidden gems Japan / #japanesefood #japanesefoodie #japanfood #japantrip"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
